LAGOS – After a resounding successful pilgrimage with Christ Apostolic Church (CAC) Worldwide, the Evangelical Church of West Africa (ECWA) worldwide has entered into a partnership with Nigeria’s foremost destination management firm, UfitFly on a pilgrims exercise tagged: ‘Beyond Pilgrimage’. The President of ECWA, Rev Stephen Baba Panya and the General Secretary, Rev Yinusa S. Nmadu disclosed to newsmen that the Universe View of ECWA worldwide had an arrangement with Ufitfly to move almost 1000 pilgrims to Israel in a trip slated for November 2022. The mega pilgrimage trip according to the ECWA President will also include an Agricultural tour, which will afford the pilgrims to tap into the agricultural technology of Israel with a view to replicate it at home when returning. Speaking in the same vein, the team leader of Ufitfly, Ajibola Ogunkeyede has assured all the intending people that will be part of the historic trip a topnotch services saying his firm is a certified Tour Operators with strong backing of Nigeria Christian Pilgrimage Commission (NCPC). “We the only Destination management company in Nigeria with unblemished records of moving Christian pilgrims from Nigeria to Israel and Jordan. “We have moved more than 3000 pilgrims after the Covid19 break without recording any absconder, am sure you will agree it is unprecedented”, said Ogunkeyede.